The time has come to demolish our bedroom. The last room of the house where nothing has been done, just a little decoration.
Remove the ugly electric fireplace and the mantel. Framing the chimney, replace the damaged plaster and sand it. Build a custom closet.
We always start with a quick sketch with pencil...
The dirty work is done.
I found several dead birds at the back of the duct; completely dried up :(
Ready for the plastering next week
Happy with the little nook on the side
Insert the new closet here (it's not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the radiator!
And we even thought about adding a lovely little air vent to prevent the chimney from taking in humidity
The chimney sweep took care of installing the cap and wind deflector. It should be a bit safer for the crows nesting up there 🪶
The plasterer has finished. We're installing the floor tomorrow!
The underlayer of cork is laid, I improvised a wood dust extractor using a roll of toilet paper as an accessory for the vacuum cleaner 😂
