Good, progress has been slow today due to delicate cuts around the door frames to achieve a smooth transition to the hallway (which is also being installed). @user45@twitter.com cursed me
Done, but on wobbly legs! Final touch: incomprehensible instructions for assembling the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
The hallway floor and baseboards still need to be done. The decorator is coming in a month, so for now, it's the bare plaster chic at home.
Short evening DIY session to remove the bottom sections of the door frames with a tenon saw or coping saw where we want the floor to fit perfectly.
The underlayer of cork in the hallway is also laid
We finished the hallway floor yesterday! Then off at 5 AM this morning to pick up Thing 1 from Heathrow, then a nap and finishing the hallway; baseboards installed. We'll take care of the caulking when the glue has set.
